    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh okay, that makes sense. a bit nerve wracking though lol. so like, if we go through with the inspection and they find something bad, like foundation issues or something, is that money stuck? can i get it back or is it basically gone if i decide not to buy the house because of the damage?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, your earnest money is not automatically lost if inspection reveals issues; that's why the inspection period is so crucial. If the inspection uncovers significant problems, you can typically use that as grounds to renegotiate, ask for repairs, or, if the issues are too serious, terminate the contract. If you terminate the contract within the agreed-upon terms due to the findings, the earnest money is usually returned to you. Always check your purchase agreement to see the specific conditions for withdrawal.",
      "source": "target",
