    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "gotcha. so the escrow agent is basically just sitting on this pile of cash waiting for everything to be okay? it feels weird that a random third party just holds onto all that money while we're waiting for the inspection and everything. what exactly is their responsibility during that time?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow agent acts as a neutral fiduciary, meaning they must handle the funds with the utmost care and according to the contract's instructions. Their primary responsibility is to safeguard your earnest money, ensuring it is not accessed by either you or the seller inappropriately. They manage the funds until all contingencies, like the inspection, are satisfied and the closing occurs. Essentially, they are the impartial custodian of the funds until the deal is finalized.",
      "source": "target",
